(43, 11, 24, 43, 5, 28, 29, 'resurrection at the last day', 'Resurrection Themes in John', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection present in both passages. Martha''s belief in the resurrection at the last day aligns with the promise of resurrection for all in John 5:28-29.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 24, 23, 26, 19, 19, 'he shall rise again in the resurrection', 'Resurrection of the Dead', 'Both passages emphasize the resurrection of the dead. Martha''s statement about the resurrection at the last day connects with Isaiah''s declaration that the dead shall arise, highlighting a shared theme of hope in life after death.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 24, 44, 17, 31, 32, 'resurrection at the last day', 'Resurrection and Judgment Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection in both passages. Martha expresses her belief in the resurrection at the last day, while Acts discusses the assurance of resurrection through Christ''s own resurrection and the coming judgment.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 24, 28, 13, 14, 14, 'rise again in the resurrection', 'Resurrection and Redemption Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection and deliverance from death. Martha''s belief in the resurrection at the last day parallels Hosea''s declaration of ransoming from the grave and death.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 24, 42, 14, 14, 14, 'resurrection at the last day', 'Resurrection of the Just', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection present in both passages. Martha expresses her belief in a future resurrection, while Luke speaks of being recompensed at the resurrection of the just.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 25, 52, 4, 14, 14, 'he that believeth in me', 'Resurrection and Belief Connection', 'Both passages emphasize belief in Jesus as central to resurrection. John 11:25 states that believers will live again, while 1 Thessalonians 4:14 assures that God will bring those who sleep in Jesus with Him.', 'theme', 0.9299999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 25, 43, 3, 36, 36, 'he that believeth in me, though he were dead, yet shall he live', 'Connection of Life and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of belief in Jesus for attaining life. John 11:25 speaks of resurrection and life, while John 3:36 contrasts belief and unbelief regarding everlasting life.', 'theme', 0.776, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 25, 62, 5, 11, 12, 'he that believeth in me, though he were dead, yet shall he live', 'Connection of Life in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of life through belief in Jesus. John 11:25 states that those who believe in Him will live, while 1 John 5:11-12 asserts that having the Son equates to having life.', 'theme', 0.727, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 25, 43, 1, 4, 4, 'the life', 'Connection of Life and Resurrection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of life. John 11:25 speaks of Jesus as the source of resurrection and life, while John 1:4 identifies Him as life itself, which illuminates humanity.', 'theme', 0.6779999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 25, 45, 8, 10, 11, 'the resurrection, and the life', 'Resurrection and Life Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of resurrection and life through faith in Christ. John 11:25 states Jesus is ''the resurrection, and the life,'' while Romans 8:10-11 discusses how the Spirit that raised Jesus will also give life to believers.', 'theme', 0.643, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 25, 23, 26, 19, 19, 'I am the resurrection, and the life', 'Resurrection and Life Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of resurrection, with John 11:25 declaring Jesus as the source of life after death, while Isaiah 26:19 speaks of the dead rising. This connection highlights the promise of life beyond death found in both texts.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 25, 45, 8, 2, 2, 'the resurrection, and the life', 'Resurrection and Life Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of life in relation to belief in Christ. John 11:25 speaks of Jesus as the source of resurrection and life, while Romans 8:2 highlights freedom from death through the Spirit of life in Christ.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 26, 43, 10, 28, 28, 'shall never die', 'Eternal Life Assurance', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of eternal life for believers. John 11:26 states that those who believe in Jesus shall never die, while John 10:28 assures that they will never perish.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 26, 43, 5, 24, 24, 'believest thou this?', 'Connection of Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of everlasting life for those who believe in Jesus. They highlight the assurance of not facing death or condemnation, reinforcing the promise of spiritual life.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 26, 45, 8, 13, 13, 'whosoever liveth and believeth in me', 'Connection of Life and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of living in relation to belief and the Spirit. John 11:26 speaks of eternal life through belief in Jesus, while Romans 8:13 contrasts living after the flesh with living through the Spirit, leading to life.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 26, 62, 5, 10, 12, 'shall never die', 'Eternal Life in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of eternal life for those who believe in Jesus. John 11:26 states that believers shall never die, while 1 John 5:12 affirms that having the Son equates to having life.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 26, 40, 9, 28, 28, NULL, 'Belief in Jesus'' Power', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of belief in Jesus. In John 11:26, belief leads to eternal life, while in Matthew 9:28, belief in Jesus'' ability to heal is affirmed by the blind men.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 26, 41, 9, 23, 23, 'believeth', 'Connection of Belief and Possibility', 'Both passages emphasize the power of belief. John 11:26 speaks of eternal life for those who believe, while Mark 9:23 highlights that all things are possible to those who believe.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 26, 40, 26, 53, 53, NULL, 'Eternal Life and Divine Power', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine assurance in both passages. John 11:26 speaks of eternal life for believers, while Matthew 26:53 emphasizes the power of prayer and divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 27, 40, 16, 16, 16, 'thou art the Christ, the Son of God', 'Confession of Christ''s Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the recognition of Jesus as the Christ and the Son of God. This connection highlights the importance of acknowledging Jesus'' divine identity in the faith of His followers.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 27, 43, 6, 14, 14, 'which should come into the world', 'Recognition of Jesus'' Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the recognition of Jesus as the one who should come into the world. In John 11:27, Martha acknowledges Jesus as the Christ, while in John 6:14, the crowd identifies Him as the prophet foretold to come.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 27, 43, 6, 69, 69, 'thou art the Christ, the Son of God', 'Confession of Faith in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize belief in Jesus as the Christ, the Son of God. This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus'' divine identity by His followers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 27, 39, 3, 1, 1, 'thou art the Christ, the Son of God', 'Connection of Messengers and Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the coming of the Lord. In John, Martha acknowledges Jesus as the Christ, while Malachi speaks of the messenger preparing the way for the Lord. This connection highlights the expectation of the Messiah''s arrival.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 27, 62, 5, 1, 1, 'thou art the Christ', 'Belief in Jesus as Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief in Jesus as the Christ. Both passages affirm that recognizing Jesus as the Christ is essential for a relationship with God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 27, 40, 11, 3, 3, 'the Christ, the Son of God', 'Connection of Messianic Expectation', 'This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus as the expected Messiah. Both passages express the belief in Jesus as ''he that should come'' and affirm his identity as the Christ.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 27, 42, 2, 11, 11, 'thou art the Christ', 'Recognition of Christ''s Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of Jesus as the Christ. In John 11:27, Martha acknowledges Jesus as ''the Christ,'' while Luke 2:11 proclaims Him as ''Christ the Lord,'' highlighting His role as Savior.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 28, 41, 10, 49, 49, 'calleth for thee', 'Calling of the Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the act of Jesus calling individuals to Him. In John, Mary is informed that ''the Master... calleth for thee,'' while in Mark, Jesus commands that the blind man be called, highlighting the personal invitation to come to Him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 28, 43, 11, 20, 20, 'The Master is come, and calleth for thee', 'Martha and Mary''s Responses', 'Both passages emphasize the contrasting responses of Martha and Mary to Jesus'' arrival. Martha actively goes to meet Jesus, while Mary remains in the house until called.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 28, 43, 13, 13, 13, 'The Master is come, and calleth for thee', 'Connection of Master and Calling', 'This connection highlights the significance of Jesus as ''Master'' in both passages. In John 11:28, Mary is called by the ''Master,'' while John 13:13 affirms His identity as ''Master and Lord.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
